Detailed Description

The section has a list of all function which need to be populated by a developers writing a custom processing chain to fit in with the DPM framework.

Typedef Documentation

typedef void(* DPM_ProcChainChirpAvailableCallbackFxn) (DPM_DPCHandle handle)

Description
This is the DPC registered function which is invoked once the chirp available interrupt has been detected.

This is a special case inject data function which indicates that chirp data is available. This is always invoked in ISR context.

Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the DPC
Return values
Notapplicable
typedef int32_t(* DPM_ProcChainDeinitFxn) (DPM_DPCHandle handle)

Description
This is the DPC registered function which is used to deinitialize the processing chain and is invoked during the DPM Deinitialization process.

Parameters
[in]handleDPC handle
Return values
Success- 0
Error- one of DPM Error Codes

typedef DPM_DPCHandle(* DPM_ProcChainInitFxn) (DPM_Handle dpmHandle, DPM_InitCfg *ptrInitCfg, int32_t *errCode)

Description
This is the DPC registered function which is used to initialize and setup the processing chain. This is invoked during the DPM Initialization process.

Parameters
[in]dpmHandleHandle to the DPM Module
[in]ptrInitCfgPointer to the initialization configuration
[out]errCodeError code populated by the API
Return values
Success- DPC Handle
Error- NULL
typedef int32_t(* DPM_ProcChainInjectDataFxn) (DPM_DPCHandle handle, DPM_Buffer *ptrBuffer)

Description
This is the DPC registered callback function which is can be used to pass input data to the processing chain to be processed. The format of the actual data buffers is DPC specific.

This function could be invoked from any execution context. It could be triggered by the application from an ISR or from another thread. Internally the DPM will notify the processing chain immediately about the buffer availability. DPC developers could either consume the buffer immediately or could process it in the DPM Framework execution context

Parameters
[in]handleHandle to the DPC
[in]ptrBufferPointer to the data buffer
Return values
Success- 0
Error- one of DPM Error Codes
typedef int32_t(* DPM_ProcChainIoctlFxn) (DPM_DPCHandle handle, uint32_t cmd, void *arg, uint32_t argLen)

Description
This is the DPC registered function which is used to configure the processing chain. DPC developers can use this to provide the ability to provide additional control capability.

NOTE: Processing Chain developers should ensure that the custom commands be offset by DPM_CMD_DPC_START_INDEX. This will ensure that there is no overlap with the standard DPM framework provided commands. If the command provided to the DPC is not within range; the DPC chain should return an error with the error code set to DPM_EINVCMD.

In addition to the DPC specific commands the following commands should also be handled by the processing chain developers:

See also
DPM_CMD_BSS_FAULT
Parameters
[in]handleDPC handle
[in]cmdCommand to be processed
[in]argCommand specific argument.
[in]argLenCommand specific argument length
Return values
Success- 0
Error- one of DPM Error Codes
